    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. Validation evidence demonstrates CFD model predicts relative hemolysis index within experimental scatter for 4 of 5 operating points. The model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Residual uncertainty in biological blood sample variability was acknowledged qualitatively during team review; the structured UQ link for the hemolysis index validation result was not completed prior to package submission, as the team considered the qualitative bounding argument sufficient. This gap does not alter the overall acceptance decision given the conservative experimental scatter bounds applied.",
